		<div id="comment_body_64213354"><p>what matters is that they do not change -- so people know what the name refers to. So what it if is named after some pompous old git or beautiful lady ?</p><p>What next: how about food, should we rename the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peach_Melba" title="wikipedia.org">Peach Melba</a> [wikipedia.org], the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sandwich#Language" title="wikipedia.org">Sandwich</a> [wikipedia.org] or <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sandwich#Language" title="wikipedia.org">Garibaldi biscuit</a> [wikipedia.org] ? Then start on drinks <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Earl_Grey_tea" title="wikipedia.org">Earl Grey tea</a> [wikipedia.org], <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tom_Collins" title="wikipedia.org">Tom Collins</a> [wikipedia.org] or <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Incredible_Hulk_(cocktail)" title="wikipedia.org">Incredible Hulk</a> [wikipedia.org]!</p><p>Have some people not got better things to do ?</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64213354">
